    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": ">Dumb - why not use the packaging repositories for each OS so you can chocolatey or apt-get the stuff?\r\n\r\nProblem is that depending on the distribution package versions may differ. At least when you use the official repositories of the distributions.\r\n\r\n> if you host LAN parties, you should also host a local repo for stuff (SMB Share) and dump the copies of whatever you'll be playing in there - its the common courtesy for your guests.\r\n\r\nThat's the idea: Create an archive everyone can use. It wouldn't matter if they run Windows, macOS or Linux. Just pull the archive from a network share, copy over the game assets and play."
